    <div class="container">
        <div class="intro">
            <h2>Your First Steps in Stock Trading</h2>
            <p>Welcome to the exciting world of stock trading! This guide will equip you with the foundational knowledge needed to embark on your trading journey.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="what-is-stock-trading">
            <h2>What is Stock Trading?</h2>
            <p>Stock trading involves buying and selling shares of publicly traded companies. Traders aim to profit from the fluctuations in stock prices.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="key-terms">
            <h2>Key Terms to Know</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Stock:</strong> A share in the ownership of a company.</li>
                <li><strong>Brokerage:</strong> A platform that facilitates the buying and selling of stocks.</li>
                <li><strong>Market Order:</strong> An order to buy or sell a stock at the current market price.</li>
                <li><strong>Limit Order:</strong> An order to buy or sell a stock at a specified price or better.</li>
                <li><strong>Dividend:</strong> A portion of a company's earnings distributed to shareholders.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="how-to-start">
            <h2>How to Start Trading</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Open a Brokerage Account:</strong>
                    <p>Choose a reputable brokerage firm and open an account. This is where you will manage your trades.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Fund Your Account:</strong>
                    <p>Transfer funds into your brokerage account to start trading. Make sure you understand any associated fees.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Research Stocks:</strong>
                    <p>Use financial news, analysis tools, and stock screener options to identify stocks youâ€™re interested in.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Practice with Virtual Trading:</strong>
                    <p>Utilize the simulation features of our game to practice trading without financial risk.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Start Trading:</strong>
                    <p>Begin with small amounts. Monitor your investments and adjust your strategies based on performance.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="trading-strategies">
            <h2>Basic Trading Strategies</h2>
            <p>As you gain experience, consider exploring different strategies:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Buy and Hold:</strong> Purchasing stocks and holding them for the long term.</li>
                <li><strong>Day Trading:</strong> Buying and selling stocks within a single trading day to capitalize on short-term market movements.</li>
                <li><strong>Value Investing:</strong> Looking for undervalued stocks that have the potential for long-term growth.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

